This is #Bitcoin 2010-2011

1) Network barely alive all through 2009
2) Wikipedia article deleted every week
3) People losing all their bitcoins because they didn't back up wallet after every send.
4) Serious security holes discovered in client v0.3
5) Nenolod attempts DOS attack

content:
2) LawAway Law

What is LayAway

Layaway is a purchase agreement where an item is reserved by the seller until the consumer completes all the payments needed to pay for that item, and only then hands over the item.

content:
1) Gift Card and Gift Certificates Law

The token is a very specific gift card that can only be used for the purchase of that diamond. 

By making the token a gift card, the token can be traded without having to KYC & Tax every trade because gift cards are close loops systems.

content:
Why #Bitcoin is like Uber

The biggest mistake people made when assessing Uber’s opportunity was modeling it as a function of the taxi market. What we failed to realize was that when you make something 100x better (ie taxi service) you take market share from surrounding markets.
renderedContent:
Why #Bitcoin is like Uber

The biggest mistake people made when assessing Uber’s opportunity was modeling it as a function of the taxi market. What we failed to realize was that when you make something 100x better (ie taxi service) you take market share from surrounding markets.

Why not just rescind the law?
